node.text: The new album is named for West’s late mother, who passed away in 2007. While DONDA explores a wider range of genres than his previous album Jesus is King, it features some of the religious themes that West has pivoted to in his recent music. A partial tracklist posted by West ahead of the release listed titles like “Pure Souls” and “Keep My Spirit Alive.” The album will be available for purchase and streaming on July 23rd.

node.text: Founded by Jeff Bezos, space travel company Blue Origin completed its first passenger flight on July 20. The rocket, named New Shepard, carried Bezos and three other passengers more than 65-miles above Earth, just to the boundary of space, known as the Kármán line. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to learn more.

node.title: @jeffbezos Completes His First Flight into Space

node.text: @gucci unveils inaugural ‘Fashion Haul’ episode for its new web series in partnership with HYPEBEAST - bringing together prominent figures to break down the luxury house’s latest designs and exploring subcultures through the world of user-generated online streaming. This episode focuses on the House’s 25 Eschatology styles as well as the new #GucciBasket sneakers.

node.title: @theshoesurgeon and @byrdmuseum kick off latest “Gucci Stream” series

node.text:
@hypebeaststyle: @wearebraindead has tapped fellow Californian label @gramicci for a relaxed outdoors-inspired series. Highlights include color-blocked pants, shorts, and six-panel hats featuring co-branded logos and purple adjustable straps. An assortment of tees sporting natural hues, bold illustrations round out the collaborative collection that's now available via Brain Dead and select stockists.⁠⁠

node.text:
@hypeart: @hbx and HypeArt will exclusively launch a print collaboration entitled ‘Shinjuku Resolution’ between @yoshirotten and Daido Moriyama. Merging Yoshirotten’s future-focused imagery with Moriyama’s iconic black and white images of everyday street scenes, the series is inspired by the pair’s ongoing exhibition of the same name taking place at the Tadao Ando-designed, @heartmuseum, and ZiWu Shanghai through September 26. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Fans can purchase works from this series exclusively at HBX.com starting August 26 at 9 PM EST. Click the link in our bio to learn more.⁠⁠
Photos: HBX

node.text:
@hypebeaststyle: 'THEM Magazine' and @supremenewyork have reunited to showcase another look at the upcoming Fall/Winter 2021 collection. Stand-out pieces featured include a further glimpse at Supreme’s upcoming New York Yankees collaboration, Skittles-themed Castelli items, as well as a puffer jacket featuring a Supreme image from the early 2000s, and of course a classic box logo hoodie. Hit the link in bio for more info.⁠⁠
Photo: @drewvickers

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @salehebembury has offered another look at his upcoming @crocs Classic Clog collaboration. The silhouette is dressed in cream white with a grooved fingerprint-like pattern extending around the entire shoe. Stay tuned for more details to come and let us know if you’ll be copping it.⁠
Photo: Salehe Bembury

node.text:
@hypefoods: @lilnasx’s relationship with @tacobell has come full circle with his new role as Chief Impact Officer. Prior to his stardom, the chart-topping artist was part of the team at an Atlanta storefront. Now, the honorary CIO title will allow him to curate a menu of innovations, collaborations and experiences surrounding the upcoming release of his album ‘Montero.’ Get more details via the link in bio.�⁠
Photo: Steve Granitz/Getty Images

node.text:
@hypebeaststyle: Consignment shop and curator @justinreed has gotten his hands on the iconic ‘DONDA’ bulletproof vest worn by @kanyewest during his August 5 listening party in Atlanta. Dressed in black with ballistic panel inserts, the 1 of 1 vest was sold for $20,000 USD. How much would you have paid?
Photo: JUSTIN REED

node.text:
#hypeAF: If you’re a diehard Joker fan, you’re in luck because @favor_gk has unveiled a baby version of the maniacal killer. The 1/6th figure comes with two exchangeable head sculpts — one with clown facepaint and one natural look — along with the DC villain’s screen-accurate red and yellow suit. Pre-order it now on Favor GK’s website for $90 USD.⁠⁠
Photo: Favor GK

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @drmartensofficial and @suicoke_official have joined forces for a one-off silhouette that combines the latter’s slip-on MURA with the former’s lightweight Lorsan outsole. Details include an easy-on, easy-off upper, a velcro heel strap, a classic Dr. Martens lightweight footbed, and the brand’s epochal yellow welt stitching. Look for it to come in two options on August 28 via the Dr. Martens website.⁠⁠
Photo: Dr. Martens/Suicoke

node.text:
@hypeart: @danielarsham will soon unveil his new collection of furniture, ‘Objects for Living: Collection II,’ at the @friedman_benda art gallery in New York City. The exhibition is a personal account of his experiences in the home throughout time, specifically how they all worked to inform his craft today. Find out more via the link in bio.⁠⁠
Photo: Daniel Arsham/Friedman Benda/Daniel Kukla
